<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-267-112  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 267 112.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  Feb 26 1990 v4 n8 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Army rejects suggestion to withdraw Tempo RFP. (theTelecommunication Modernization project intended to modernizeDefense Department telephone systems throughout the Washington,DC, area)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McCloskey, Paul N.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A recommendation by the Defense Department's inspector general(IG) that the Pentagon withdraw its RFP for the $610 millionTelecommunication Modernization (Tempo) project intended tomodernize Defense Department telephone systems in the Washington,DC, area was rejected by the Army.andP;  The IG's report on its specialinvestigation on charges that competition was excluded from thecontract was full of errors and did not justify therecommendations, according to the Army.andP;  The Tempo RFP issued inMay 1988 called for a 10-year single-source contract to replacethe DOD's National Capital Region Network based on a 95,000-lineCentrex system from Chesapeake andamp; Potomac Telephone Co (Candamp;P) andusing 195,000 ATandamp;T telephones.andP;  The IG claims that 22 prospectivecontract bidders it interviewed said they would not bid on thecontract because terms favored Candamp;P; several barriers tocompetition were cited in the IG report.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Competitive BiddingCommunications Service SuppliersCommunications EquipmentGovernment ContractsNational GovernmentDefense ContractsRequest for ProposalsUpgradingTelephone SystemsTelecommunicationsContractorsUnited States. Department of Defense.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>